k tie  black cummerbund or vest  and black shoes  or mess dress if so desired by respective military personnel  Cadets attending the Ring Figure Ball who are not members of the Class of 2017 will wear coatee and ducks  long skirt for females  This  criteria will be strictly adhered to  Failure to meet the this criteria will result in not being allowed to walk through the Ring at the Ball  Ring Figure Policy General Order 81   VMI Class Ring   Ring Figure Eligibility Policy Class Dues Refund If you are dismissed for academic  disciplinary  or Honor Code violations   NO REFUND If you decide not to attend Ring Figure  but stay at VMI   NO REFUND If you leave VMI for personal or financial reasons see the Class Treasurer  Ring Figure Info Ring Figure Home  Class Leadership  Policies  Event Schedule  Date Schedule  Parent Schedule  What to Wear  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 